<br>
~Drunk and disorderly he stumbles to the adventurers at hand~<br>
<br>
    Hey, you wanted evil? HERE I AM!!!<br>
<br>
~cackles insanely and incessantly~<br>
<br>
    Being a powerful and old wizard...<br>
<br>
~starts counting on his fingers realizing he doesn't have 758 fingers~<br>
<br>
...uh I have a tendency to forget....uh....stuff<br>
<br>
~growing angry because of his words tripping on themselves he takes the barmaid and showers her in rain of fire destroying her instantly~<br>
<br>
Ah, very well. What is it about death that makes me feel so complete and well?<br>
<br>
~looks once again at the adventures now somewhat more sober~<br>
<br>
   If you have need for me you know where to find me...<br>
<br>
~as he walks out the emblazoned crimson fist shows on the back of his robes~ <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub96.ezboard.com/uvicarbalomar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>VicarBalomar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Whispering Scythe Guild member</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#E6E8fA>(10/12/01 3:54:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub96.ezboard.com/fscythe72844frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Someone Asked for help?</span><hr size=1> Balomar immediately pushes back his chair and rises from his seat his face flushing with anger.<br>
<br>
He doesn't even pause to glance over the fallen body of the barmaid merely shouts in a strangled voice.<br>
<br>
&quot;May the power of Brell Serillis strike you down!!&quot; and swings his arms forward in a broad arc.  Immediately the ageing wizard is surrounded by a the crackling electrical fury of the wrath of a god.<br>
<br>
A loud crack sounds thoughout the tavern and the doors are blown open by the explosion.<br>
<br>
As the smell of ozone lingers in the air and electricity moves up and down the spine of everyone present, the sound of running feet and the shouts of guards can be heard approaching the tavern.<br>
<br>
Balomar heafts the dark ember hammer above his head and waits for the wizard to make his move as his fellow guildmates gape at him in stunned astonishment. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub96.ezboard.com/ugiliganvenificus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Giligan Venificus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Citizen of Morell Thule</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#E6E8fA>(10/12/01 4:11:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub96.ezboard.com/fscythe72844frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Someone Asked for help?</span><hr size=1> Quickly the erudite enchanter steps from his place at the table and makes a quick gesture and mutters something under his breath.<br>
<br>
<br>
~~~~Balomar vanishes~~~~~<br>
<br>
With a sly grin Giligan returns to his seat and nods at the wizard.<br>
<br>
The guards are coming? Are you going to be here to greet them?<br>
<br>
Giligan takes a sip of his drink.<br>
<br>
I don't think we asked for any evil.  I am sure the guards didn't. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub96.ezboard.com/uarrington.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arrington</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.whisperingscythe.org/images/ws3.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Whispering Scythe Guild member</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#E6E8fA>(10/13/01 11:31:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub96.ezboard.com/fscythe72844frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Someone Asked for help?</span><hr size=1> &quot;Evil???&quot; the shocked gnome mutters.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :eek --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/eek.gif ALT=":eek"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Yes, some did ask to find evil to fight in MistMoore.  However, this is not evil.  <br>
<br>
Evil and good have purpose, was the barmaid the daughter of a local elder?  Did she have a pure heart that even our vicar could not see?  Maybe she held the key to a lock found on some evil monster.  Are natural occurrences like lightning or a storm evil?  They kill just as quickly and as easily, but they are not evil.  No more evil than a train wreck.  <br>
<br>
Many believe all that is not good is evil. However, that is the definition of a lazy madman.  Evil is purposely doing something bad to create a wicked end.  You think making me mad is evil?  My mother has made me mad many times.  I grow angry at a long travel and even sometimes at my waistline.  I can ask the local church, but I am sure none of these things are evil.  <br>
<br>
This sir was done to create chaos, to make someone innocent pay.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :x --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/sick.gif ALT=":x"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   We did not order that.  <br>
<br>
However, this has been served, and mama always said to finish what is on my plate.  Tell me, does your spell work as well on another wizard?  It will not be the first time I was chased out of Kelethin for fighting.  They always welcomed me back in the past.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :smokin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smokin.gif ALT=":smokin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
/em lights up the sky with his response<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
/ooc  Dude, cool.  A little action.    <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub96.ezboard.com/umenludarja.showPublicProfile?language=EN>menludarja</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.whisperingscythe.org/images/ws3.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Whispering Scythe Guild leader</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#E6E8fA>(10/15/01 8:36:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub96.ezboard.com/fscythe72844frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.praetoria.homestead.com/files/EQ_Head_Shot.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Someone Asked for help?</span><hr size=1> Menludarja hears the crack and explosion form the guild hall three platforms away.<br>
<br>
I rush to the window of the guild hall and look out over the platforms below and see the sparkling red twinkle of lights amassed in and around the Heartwood tavern below me.<br>
<br>
Realizing many of the Scythe frequent that bar, I rush forth from the guild hall and quickly run across the bridge and down the ramp toward the tavern.  Before I can get on to the second bridge my way is cut off by a dozen guards running at the tavern.<br>
<br>
By the blessing of Tunare, I mutter, What have they done now?  First a naked barbarian, then a drunken mess, followed by a visit from a Tier'Dahl.  Now someone has brought the retribution of a god down in the tavern.  They will never let us in Kelethin again if this continues.<br>
<br>
After the guards have passed, I quickly ask Tunare to give me the spirit of the wolf and I follow them with a ll due speed to the Heartwood Tavern.  Wondering what I will find. <p>Menludarja Pathtaker<br>
Ranger of Tunare<br>
Guildleader fo the Whispering Scythe<br>Somewhere ages and ages hence: <br>
Two roads diverged in a wood, and I-- <br>
I took the one less traveled by, <br>
And that has made all the difference.<br> 

</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub96.ezboard.com/umenludarja.showPublicProfile?language=EN>menludarja</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.whisperingscythe.org/images/ws3.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Whispering Scythe Guild leader</span><br>  Posts: 63<br> <font color=#E6E8fA>(10/30/01 9:04:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub96.ezboard.com/fscythe72844frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.praetoria.homestead.com/files/EQ_Head_Shot.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Someone Asked for help?</span><hr size=1> At long last, in what seems like days since the loud crack reverberated through the city of Kelethin, I reach the doors to the Heartwood tavern.  Uulavin, the barmaid lays dead on the floor, several of the guild members are sitting and standing about our usual table in the corner.  The guards begin to empty the tavern.<br>
<br>
&quot;What is going on here,&quot; I ask Guard Dayblaze who is an old friend.<br>
<br>
&quot;We will need to investigate this.&quot; He replies grimly.  &quot;I have known you since childhood, but I cannot let a death go unnoticed.  I will let you know what we find out, but I would also make sure you talk with your guildmates.  I hope the evil of the TierDal has not penetrated into the city itself.&quot;<br>
<br>
I nod at Guard Dayblaze.<br>
<br>
Grimly I gather together the member's of the Scythe and we return to the Guild House for a more somber night.<br>
<br>
After hearing what happened from all who were present, I let them know, &quot;We have been given a weighty responsiblity in guarding the Scythe for Kelethin.  It seems evil is seeking us out, we must be ever vigilant.  Keep your eyes sharp as the days go by.&quot; <p><B>Menludarja Pathtaker</B><br>
Ranger of Tunare<br>
Guildleader of <A HREF="http://www.whisperingscythe.org">Whispering Scythe</A><br>Somewhere ages and ages hence: <br>
Two roads diverged in a wood, and I-- <br>
I took the one less traveled by, <br>
And that has made all the difference.<br> 

